{
  "name": "RPlog_To_Hire_a_Smuggler",
  "title": "An Open Line to a Free Trader",
  "summary": "Idling aboard his ship the Hirakiis and trawling SmugglerNet for a big score, the freelance smuggler Jaspar Andromidas takes an unexpected holocall from Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard of the New Republic. She makes her pitch plainly: she needs an independent captain to slip the Imperial blockade choking the Caspia system and ferry humanitarian supplies -- food, water, medicine, possibly ammunition -- to its embattled inhabitants. The two haggle over the 'going rate for grease,' interrupted by Ambrosia's overeager protocol droid, which she silences with a thump. They settle on forty-five thousand credits up front for Jaspar (thirty-five for any associates he recruits) plus three to five thousand per run from the Navy, with Ambrosia promising scouted safe-landing terrain and coordination with the CDU's Presav so he won't take friendly fire. She warns that assassins may target her and provides backup contacts, including Captain Rasi Cen, before transferring the funds -- briefly shielding a dark-haired child from the holocam's view -- and wishing Jaspar the Force. The smuggler accepts, terminating the call convinced it may be the best decision he's ever made.",
